summary: Omfg this is what I've been waiting for okay Carol x reader where they're both singing karaoke together like in those scenes...
question: Omfg this is what I've been waiting for okay Carol x reader where they're both singing karaoke together like in those scenes where she's with Maria at the bar
answer:
⋆ GOOD TIMES

pairing: carol danvers x reader

a/n: I hope you like this dude!! thank you for the request!!!! :—-)

The music in the bar was loud, bass vibrating through your body as you danced with a drink in your hand. You could feel Carol’s eyes on you as she stood at the counter, finishing off her own drink before asking for another. There was a smile plastered on your face, cheeks flushed in the best way as you glance over your shoulder at her. 

“Come here!” you shouted, knowing damn well she wouldn’t be able to hear you over the music. So you motioned for her to come closer.

With little resistance, you watched Carol float over to you, pushing through other drunken bodies. 

The two of you were regulars here, the owners and bartenders knew who you were and what you liked to drink without asking. This little place was your safe haven. A place for you to flourish, to be yourself without judgement. 

Carol’s arms wrapped around your midsection as she pressed your back against her chest, swaying in time with you. You could feel the alcohol running through your system, powering you to be more bold, more confident. 

A laugh fell from your lips as Carol’s hands traveled up and down your sides, her movements soft and warm. Glancing around at the other patrons, you saw the usual crowd. Bikers and their wives, single guys flirting with women who had no interest in them and old men drinking whiskey and singing along with the music. It brought a smile to your face, head leaning back against Carol’s shoulder as a drunken giggle left your lips.

“Lets sing!” you mumble, a bright smile gracing your lips. Spinning around, you wrapped your arms around Carol’s neck, cocking a brow at her as a smirk made its way onto your face.

“A duet? Hmm I’m more of a solo star myself.” Carol joked, loving the slight pout of your lips. “But… I guess I could make one exception…”

“Holding out for a hero?” You asked, taking your bottom lip between your teeth to prevent the smile from taking over your features. You watched Carol chuckle, her tongue darting out as she considers your request.

“Hell yes. Let’s do it.”

blog.name: lavibele
blog.title: The invisibility of the Bird.
blog.description: she/her | 21 y/o | ravenclaw | bi | multifandom | my mind in other peoples words | feel free to talk to me

body:
I just watched Captain Marvel

I like the marvel movies because they always have a sense of breaking down and getting back up again,

A sense of never giving up,

Of fighting for what you believe in

Of getting hurt and becoming stronger because of it.

But this.. Captain Marvel..

She didn’t get beaten down by her enemies, she got beaten down by the people she was supposed to trust. Her peers. Her colleagues.

They told her no. They said she is too emotional. She wasn’t allowed to fly an airplane because “You do know why they call it the cockpit, right?”

And she said yes.

She embraced her emotions.

She said “I can do this”

And she did.

I am curious to see, what if woman stopped listening to the negativity of men? What if we embraced our emotions?

Maybe men have pushed us down, because they KNOW they can’t handle us at our fullest, emotional capacity.

I think, if we all embraced our emotions, we would be capable of great things.

If we embraced our emotions, we could become the godesses that we actually always have been.
